Productivity was calculated using the following equation:p=mt2−mt1/t2−t1t2>t1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ p=\left(\mathrm{m}\mathrm{t}2-\mathrm{m}\mathrm{t}1\right)/\left(t2-t1\right)t2>t1 $$\end{document}where mt1 and mt2 are the biomass concentrations at the different time points (t1 and t2), respectively.
